race.comment: Great little race, with five of the seven being last start winners and the other two scoring two back. PIMLICO (6) broke through last start over this distance at Kembla after stalking the pace. Draws in closer today. Getting better with racing and is ready to go to this next level. CASSEROUSSE (8) returned from a 28-week spell with an impressive maiden win over 1100m at Hawkesbury recently. Travelled on the speed that day and showed great courage late. Strips fitter and will give them something to catch. Last start Beaumont winner ZOCKETMAN (4) is pushing for early favouritism on the back of that dominant victory when resuming. Unbeaten and they haven't got to the bottom of him yet. NITRO (1) came from a long way back to just arrive in time on debut over this distance at Warwick Farm last time out. Promising three-year-old from an in-form stable. ZEBRA FINCH (3) is a new acquisition for Ciaron Maher fresh from a five-month spell. Betting the key.
